Diagnosis. Pronotum relatively short, 0.75–0.81 X as long as wide; anterior margin of prothorax in front of procoxa angulately projecting; mesosternum with apically rounded, cone-shaped protrusion directed anteriad (
Fig. 77
); protibia in female (
Fig. 135
) with dorsal contour evenly convex; mesotibia in male (
Fig. 128
) with subapical dorsal extension short, dentiform; ventrite 4 in male in middle with inconspicuous transverse row of suberect setae (
Figs. 95–96
); aedeagus with apical scoop of pedon (
Fig. 156
) pointed.

Head (
Fig. 114
) short. Gena 0.66 x as long as width of head behind eyes. Vertex microreticulate, markedly rugose-punctate. Eyes dorsally contiguous in middle for 0.7 x their length. Ventral surface markedly transversely rugose, anteriorly near eye with few interspersed punctures.

Proventriculus (
Fig. 102
) with eight primary folds bearing spiniform processes.

Elytron 2.15 x longer than wide; intervals weakly shining, somewhat dull, with distinct coriarious sculpture of irregularly transverse wrinkles (
Fig. 88
).

Legs. Procoxa 0.89 x as long as wide; approaching anterior margin of prothorax; in anterior aspect coxae with inner contour diverging in convex line; anterior surface microreticulate, sparsely shallowly punctate. Protibia with dorsal contour evenly convex; uncus subventral. Mesotibia (
Fig. 128
) with subapical dorsal extension acute, subtriangularly dentiform.

Abdomen. Venter flat, surface medially sparsely punctate, sparsely setose with recumbent setae; ventrite 4 in middle with inconspicuous transverse row of suberect setae pointing backwards (
Figs. 95–96
). Pygidium 1.08 x wider than long.

Terminalia. Sternite VIII (
Fig. 164
) medially subdivided by membrane connecting lateral sclerotised areas; apex broadly bilobate, densely setose with long setae; base medially with marked constriction. Tegminal plate as in
Fig. 157
. Aedeagus with sclerotised sides of pedon widening mesoapicad, connected to subtriangular plate fused with its short side to apical scoop, the latter (
Fig. 156
) ca. 1.14 x longer than wide, sides sinuate and converging, apex pointed; tectum with sides converging, apically pointed; TA (
Figs. 154–155
) flagelliform, insertion of ductus ejaculatorius ventral; basal sclerite long, narrow, folded dorsoapicad, dorsally fitting to basal half of long, C-shaped flagellum formed by fusion of extended transferprocesses. Endophallus with cuticle densely minutely denticulate.

Distribution (
Fig. 188
). INDIA , Karnataka (Molem), Tamil Nadu (Nilgiri Hills). Elevation: 900–1000 m .
